cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.PL

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, to optimize computer hardware architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Architecture), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as these sub-categories are closely related to the use of machine learning in computer architecture. The sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also possible as they involve the use of neural networks and programming language optimizations, respectively, which are relevant to the paper's topic.
